name: Hidden Bridge Canyon
description:
Introduction

AN AMAZING NATURAL BRIDGE. THAT WE JUST CAME ACROSS NOT KNOWING IT WAS THERE. VERY IMPRESSIVE FEATURE IN DEATH VALLEY. FOUND OUT LATER THAT IT HAD BEEN DISCOVERED MANY DECADES AGO, BUT SOME PEOPLE WERE WANTING TO KEEP IT A SECRET. THE CANYON ALSO HAD SOME OLD WEBBING ANCHORS AND PITONS TOO, SO IT WAS NO FIRST DESCENT FOR US. A VERY WORTHY SIGHT TO GO SEE.

Approach

THREE OPTIONS HERE - ONE IS THE HIGH ROAD TRAIL AND COME DOWN THE UPPER PORTION OF THE CANYON, OR COME THE VALLEY FLOOR ROUTE TO THE WASH, OR THIRD, YOU CAN COME UP "ONE DROP CANYON" AND BY-PASS THE DROP

Descent

Exit

TWO EXIT OPTIONS, AND I HAVE BEEN DOWN BOTH OF THEM. FIRST OPTION, IS JUST CONTINUE DOWN THE WASH TO THE MAIN DV CANYON FLOOR AND HEAD BACK TO THE START FOR 7.3 MILES. OR THE SECOND OPTION IS TO CLIMB UP A LITTLE AND HEAD OUT BY USING "ONE DROP CANYON" WHICH IS LISTED HERE IN THE BETA. IT ONLY HAS ONE TECHNICAL DROP AND CAN EASILY BY-PASSED ON THE WAY OUT

Red tape
